title: Panic: forcing query with already existing `DepNode`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code I'm sorry, but trying to minimize from here is going to take longer than I can afford to spend. The best I can do is open this ticket and point to the code: https://github.com/martinthomson/raw-ipa/commit/c8390ab0caac848b524ed9ee9638c0eb4d444c53 Note that the snapshot I provided here does not compile, but then it won't crash the compiler either in most cases. This seems to be an interaction with incremental compilation. Running `cargo clean` makes the problem go away. I don't have exact STR for getting into the necessary state for reproducing the bug. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.2 (9eb3afe9e 2023-03-27) binary: rustc commit-hash: 9eb3afe9ebe9c7d2b84b71002d44f4a0edac95e0 commit-date: 2023-03-27 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.2 LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'forcing query with already existing `DepNode` ``` ...more in the details (there is a lot).
